d><td valign=top bgcolor=#DEEFDE class=headings><font color=#006400>Comment</font></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#DEEFDE><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub18.ezboard.com/usolitudedragon.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Solitude Dragon</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>MithMarr Apprentice</span><br>  Posts: 11<br> <font color=#006400>(1/14/02 3:50:41 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub18.ezboard.com/fmithanielmarrdailynewsfrm11.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=987.topic&index=44>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   THIS IS WHAT I'VE BEEN TALKING ABOUT!</span><hr size=1> Although I didn't put it as eloquently as Utnayan does, I'll try to do so now.<br>
<br>
DAoC was the "Holy Grail"...the shining new banner of MMORPG's when Mythic first released information about it. It was going the be the next generation of online gaming. In essense, EQ in a pretty red dress.<br>
<br>
Unfortunately, that didn't happen. I was all for this game, but due to UO and EQ, I was cautious about buying a new game til about a month or so after it came out.<br>
<br>
DAMN right I was angry when I read the vnboards. Apparently all this company knows to do is to shovel shit up your ass since <b>they didn't make their own engine!</b><br>
<br>
If a company promises stuff, they need to deliver. Online gaming is apparently the exception to the rule because the starved, hungry idiots (fanbois) who play these games don't seem to see the truth sometimes. If a game sucks, you need to call the company on it. Granted, the best way to do it isn't to bitch at them, but there's one thing DAoC has that the previous games didn't have: a good honest look at how <b>not</b> to screw the hell up.<br>
<br>
They up and did it anyway.<br>
<br>
