<br>
I fired up DAoC shortly after release.  Took a month off EQ almost to try it out.  Rolled me up a Albion armsman and proceeded to go kill stuff.  Funny thing was, I don't remember once even camping an item, having a difficult quest and by the time I got my lvl 15 xbow skill I realized just how BORING it was there.  Every single piece of highly coveted equipment I already owned, most of it from soloing, as a TANK!<br>
<br>
DAoC is a textbook perfect example of what happens when a game company gives in to the whiners, period.  Don't want camps? Want everything handed to you?  Want to log on and just go about the same boring thing whenever you want with no hard work, no CR's, no strategy?  Viola! we'll make you DAoC! Now pay us 12 bucks a month and be happy, because we think this surely must be what you want. While we're at it, we'll make it so you can walk into any job you want with no resume and a dirty T-shirt and barefeet and just get the job too.  Oh wait, let's give you a brand new Mercedes as well for nothing, Im' sure you don't mind that everyone else drives one too.<br>
<br>
The 51+ game isnt anything like the lower levels, it takes committment, strategy, teamwork, and the thrive of a challenge.  Ut said he got disatisfied at lvl 40+, I don't know how he made it that long, I couldnt get past lvl 20. <br>
<br>
I think Daoc above all did a GREAT service to Verant by shoving their product out early, they proved that although we all thought that was what we wanted, we were shocked to find out a great many of the things we hated in EQ are what MAKES A GAME GOOD.  It took Daoc to show us that, thank you Mythic.<br>
<br>
When I look at my epic that I got at lvl 53, and I think about the 20+ people who scrambled from 3 different continents at 3am to help me kill Ragefire for it, I am *thankful* for the way things are in EQ.  It has value, every single item I wear has a story, a new friendship, a memory behind it and it gives the game more depth and meaning than can be expressed.<br>
<br>
Until a game company realizes just how much that adds to a game, honestly I don't think anyone will ever unseat EQ.<br>
<br>
So, all of you that want to complain and ra ra on DAoC, and especially that total idiot who doesnt want us &quot;hogging his bandwidth because we are always on&quot; I hope you stay over there and be happy, we'll stay over here in this challenging yet rewarding world of Norrath and continue to have FUN.<br>
